<h1>News about Debian for S/390</h1>

<h3><:=spokendate ("2001-07-08"):></h3>

<p>
Several people attended the talk by Richard Higson.  This suddenly lead into a notice of
intention by some developers, some people working for IBM and the Stuttgart based company
<a href="http://www.trustsec.de/">trustsec IT solutions GmbH</a> who now plan to work on
getting Debian GNU/Linux officially supported by IBM on the S/390 architecture, alongside
with other distributions.

<h3><:=spokendate ("2001-07-06"):></h3>

<p>
<a href=mailto:richard.higson@gt.owl.de>Richard Higson</a> gave a talk about <a
href="http://pax.gt.owl.de/~higson/LinuxTag2001/Deb390-talk.html">Debian on S/390</a> and
a demonstration of the current status of this port at the <a
href="http://www.infodrom.ffis.de/Debian/events/LinuxTag2001/day.php3">Debian Day</a>
during <a href="http://www.linuxtag.org/2001/english/">LinuxTag 2001</a>. (Motto: "Where
.com meets .org").

<h3><:=spokendate ("2001-06-02"):></h3>

<p>Gerhard Tonn <a
href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-s390-0105/msg00018.html">announced</a> the beginnings
of an S/390 autobuilder, hosted and sponsored by <a
href="http://www.millenux.de/company">Mi||enux</a>, (the makers of <a
href="http://linux.s390.org">Think Blue Linux</a> for IBM's <a
href="http://www-1.ibm.com/servers/s390/pes/">S/390</a> series and <a
href="http://www.zseries.org">Think Blue 64 Linux</a> for IBM's <a
href="http://www-1.ibm.com/servers/eserver/zseries/900.html">z/Series</a>).  We owe
special thanks to Fritz Elfert for taking the time and trouble to support "a competing
distribution".

<p>The <a
href="ftp://source.rfc822.org/pub/mirror/s390-ibm-linux/debian-s390/base-s390.tar.gz">
base-s390.tar.gz</a> can be used as a chroot environment on a standard S/390 <a
href="ftp://source.rfc822.org/pub/mirror/s390-ibm-linux/debian-s390/image-2.2.19+ctc+rdr.gz">
linux-2.2.19</a> or later kernel. This one is generated with builtin CTC support, and
IPL's from RDR (after unzipping ;-).

